
                                            Police say a second officer was wounded.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - A police officer has been shot dead at an ice cream shop in Port Elizabeth on Friday. Police say a second officer was wounded. The incident happened when officers responded to an alarm in North End. Police spokesperson Sandra Janse van Rensburg said: “At this stage, there is no arrest and we’re still busy with our investigation. If there is anyone with information, they can contact the police.”